Hence we start by generating plots that show the maximum achievable concentration
of probability at the searched-for site as a function of $\gamma$.
For instance, for $l=1$ we would see sharp peaks with their maxima
quickly converging to $(\gamma_{*},p_{\text{max}})=(1.0,0.5)$ as $n\rightarrow\infty$.
Let us denote the $\gamma$ coordinates of those maxima by $\gamma'_{*}$.
Fig.~\ref{fig.p2gammas} allows to read off $\gamma'_{*}$ for
